Colossus (Spirit Temple).text: This hint is in another castle.

DMC (Bombable Wall).text: Dodongo's Cavern is much easier and faster to clear as Adult.

DMC (Upper Grotto).text: They say that tossing a bomb will cause a Blue Bubble to go after it.

DMT (Biggoron).text: Did you know that the Kokiri Sword is as effective as Deku Sticks against Dead Hand?

Dodongos Cavern (Bombable Wall).text: Having trouble breathing underwater?^Have you tried wearing more BLUE?

GC (Maze).text: Did you know that the solution to the Truth Spinner in Shadow Temple is never one of the two positions closest to the initial position?

GC (Medigoron).text: They say Ingo is not very good at planning ahead.

GV (Waterfall).text: Why are you asking me? I don't have any answers! I'm just as confused as you are!

Graveyard (Shadow Temple).text: Did you know that Ruto is strong enough to defeat enemies and activate ceiling switches inside Jabu Jabu's Belly?

HC (Malon).text: Don't believe in yourself. Believe in the me that believes in you!

HC (Rock Wall).text: When all else fails, use Fire.

HC (Storms Grotto).text: For you, the day you read this hint was the most important day of your life.^But for me, it was Tuesday.

HF (Cow Grotto).text: They say that the Lizalfos in Dodongo's Cavern like to play in lava.

HF (Near Market Grotto).text: @ tries to read the Gossip Stone...^${12 48 06}but he's standing on the wrong side of it!

HF (Open Grotto).text: They say that Anju needs to stop losing her chickens.

HF (Southeast Grotto).text: Can you move me? I don't get great service here.

KF (Deku Tree Left).text: Did you know that Dark Link's max health is equal to @'s max health?

KF (Deku Tree Right).text: Master, there is a 0 percent chance that this hint is useful in any way.

KF (Outside Storms).text: I am the King of Gossip Stones, but fear not - I have the common touch! That means I can make conversation with everyone^from foreign dignitaries to the lowliest bumpkin - such as yourself!

KF (Storms Grotto).text: They say Ganon's tail is vulnerable to nuts, arrows, swords, explosives, hammers...^...sticks, seeds, boomerangs...^...rods, shovels, iron balls, angry bees...

Kak (Open Grotto).text: They say that Barinade fears Deku Nuts.

LH (Lab).text: They say that in the castle courtyard you can see a portrait of a young Talon.

LH (Southeast Corner).text: They say that bombing the hole Volvagia last flew into can be rewarding.

LH (Southwest Corner).text: It would be a shame if something... unfortunate... were to happen to you.^Have you considered saving lately?

LW (Bridge).text: They say that Flare Dancers do not fear Goron-crafted blades.

LW (Near Shortcuts Grotto).text: They say that the final item you're looking for can be found somewhere in Hyrule.

SFM (Maze Lower).text: They say Ganondorf knows where to find the instrument of his doom.

SFM (Maze Upper).text: Without the Lens of Truth, the Treasure Chest Mini-Game is a 1 out of 32 chance.^Good luck!

SFM (Saria).text: They say that Ganondorf will appear in the next Mario Tennis.

ToT (Left).text: They say all toasters toast toast.

ToT (Left-Center).text: I love to gossip! Wanna be friends?

ToT (Right).text: They say that if you don't use your slingshot at all when you play the slingshot minigame, the owner gets upset with you.

ToT (Right-Center).text: Hi! I'm currently on an exchange program from Termina.^They say that East Clock Town is on the way of the hero.

ZD (Mweep).text: Ya ha ha! You found me!

ZF (Fairy).text: We don't make mistakes, we have happy accidents.

ZF (Jabu).text: Gossip Stone Shuffle must be on. I'm normally in Zora's Domain!

ZR (Near Domain).text: May the way of the Hero lead to the Triforce.

ZR (Near Grottos).text: Gorons are stupid. They eat rocks. Except, apparently, the big rock blocking Dodongo's Cavern.

ZR (Open Grotto).text: They say that most of the water in Hyrule flows through King Zora's buttocks.
